troversies in the U.S. directly, exploring the transformative roles played by a host of neglected figures in the development of modern and postmodern American culture.The diversity of American Jewry means that there is no single explanation for Jews' interventions in this field. Rejecting generalizations, this bookoffers case studies that pair cultural histories with close readings of both contested texts and trial transcripts to reveal the ways in which specific engagements with obscenity mattered to particular American Jews at discrete historical moments.Reading American culture from Theodore Dreiser and Henry Miller to Curb Your Enthusiasm and FCC v. Fox, Unclean Lips analyzes the variable historical and cultural factors that account for the central role Jews have played in the struggles over obscenity and censorship in the modern United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aAmerican fictionxHistory and criticismx20th century. 0aAmerican fictionxJewish authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aCensorshipxUnited States. 0aCensorshipzUnited States. 0aErotic comic books, strips, etcxHistory and criticismxUnited States. 0aErotic comic books, strips, etczUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 0aObscene wordsvHumor. 0aObscenity (Law)xUnited States. 0aObscenity (Law)zUnited States. 0aPornographyxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aPornographyxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aWords, ObscenexHumor. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479851584423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479851584.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL